<title>TURKEY: Turk Petkim Q1 profits fall 20.4 pct.</title>
<headline>Turk Petkim Q1 profits fall 20.4 pct.</headline>
<dateline>ISTANBUL 1997-04-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Jan-March 1997 provisional</p>
<p>(billion lira unless stated)</p>
<p>    Per share profit (lira) 1,932.77 vs   2,427.74</p>
<p>    Net profit		  5,798.30 vs   7,283.21</p>
<p>    Net sales		  23,938.67 vs  14,351.65</p>
<p>    Operating profit	  2,461.42 vs   3,874.00</p>
<p>    Exceptional income	8,183.78 vs   9,076.80</p>
<p>    Exceptional expense	 182.22 vs     121.78</p>
<p>    Interest paid		 131.38 vs     164.64</p>
<p>    Extraordinary expense     744.72 vs     333.44</p>
<p>    Total debts		49,521.99 vs  44,312.00</p>
<p>    Equity		     95,873.62 vs  62,556.28</p>
<p>    Capital		     3,000.00 vs   3,000.00</p>
<p>NOTE - Turkey's largely state-owned petrochemicals giant Petkim-Petrokimya Holding A.S. is slated for partial sell off, with 96 percent of its shares held by the privatisation administration OIB.</p>
<p>It will distribute a 6,400 lira cash dividend per 1,000 lira nominal-valued share from 1996 profits from May 23. The dividend payout will total 19.2 trillion lira.</p>
<p>The figures above do not take into account Turkey's 77 percent annual wholesale in March.</p>
<p>-- Istanbul newsroom +90-212-2750875.</p>
</text>
